* $$s$$ â€“ ''nonnegative'' simple function in the form $$s = \displaystyle\sum_{i=1}^n \alpha_i \chi_{A_i}$$
* $$R$$ - $$\sigma$$-algebra, $$E \in R$$

We define 
$$ 
\int_E s\:d\mu = \sum_{i=1}^n\alpha_i\mu(A_i\cap E)$$ 

for measurable simple function and

$$ 
\int_E f\:d\mu = \sup \int_E s\:d\mu$$

for other measurable functions (including simple)

Also:
$$ 
\int_E f\:d\mu = \int_X \chi_E f \: d\mu$$

! Properties
#
#> $$\displaystyle\int_E (s + t)\:d\mu = \int_E s\:d\mu + \int_E t\:d\mu$$
# [[Lebesgue's Monotone Convergence Theorem]] 
#> $$\displaystyle f_n \to f \implies \displaystyle \int_X f_n d\mu \to \int_X f d\mu$$
#
#> $$\displaystyle\int_E \sum_{i=1}^\infty\:d\mu = \sum_{i=1}^\infty \int_E s\:d\mu$$
# ''Fatou Lemma''
#>$$\displaystyle\int_X (\liminf_{n\to \infty}f_n)\:d\mu \le \liminf_{n\to \infty} \int_X f_n \: d\mu$$
# $$\displaystyle\varphi(E) = \int_E f\:d\mu\quad$$ is a [[measure|Measure]] and
